  "prompt": "Why do gel nails get stained? How do you prevent this from happening?",
  "response": "Gel nails can get stained for several reasons:\n\nCauses of staining:\n1. Dark or highly pigmented nail polish colors\n2. Exposure to certain foods (turmeric, curry, berries)\n3. Hair dyes or chemical products\n4. Not using a base coat\n5. Low-quality gel polish\n6. Prolonged UV/LED lamp exposure\n\nPrevention methods:\n1. Always apply a clear base coat before colored polish\n2. Use high-quality gel polish brands\n3. Wear gloves when handling staining substances\n4. Use cuticle oil to protect nails\n5. Apply thin, even layers of polish\n6. Avoid leaving gel polish on for extended periods\n7. Use a pH-balancing primer before application\n8. Clean nails thoroughly before gel application\n9. Use a UV-protective top coat\n10. Gently buff out light stains\n\nRemoval of stains:\n1. Gentle nail polish remover\n2. Whitening toothpaste\n3. Lemon juice\n4. Baking soda paste\n5. Professional nail treatment\n\nBy following these preventive measures, you can minimize gel nail staining and maintain a clean, professional appearance.",
